- Sat 27 Jul 2019. Saudi Arabia
[Telegraph Star, abridged, edited]
https://telegraphstar.com/saudi-arabia-suspends-visas-to-pilgrims-from-congo-fearing-spread-of-ebola/

Saudi Arabia has suspended issuing visas to pilgrims from the Democratic Republic of the Congo over fears that Ebola could spread during next month's [August 2019] Hajj pilgrimage there.

Wed [24 Jul 2019] morning, a note issued by the Saudi Ministry of Foreign Affairs cited last week's move by the World Health Organization (WHO) to declare the Ebola outbreak in DRC's eastern North Kivu and Ituri provinces a public health emergency of international concern. WHO has pleaded to all countries to not impose a ban on any country on account of Ebola being widespread, but Saudi Arabia has ignored this plea from WHO, keeping its citizens' safety above international relations.

